{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":480,"text":"The narrative of a rising Africa\nis being challenged."}]},{"cues":[{"time":4360,"text":"About 10 years ago,\nI spoke about an Africa,"},{"time":8840,"text":"an Africa of hope and opportunity,"},{"time":11560,"text":"an Africa of entrepreneurs,"},{"time":13520,"text":"an Africa very different from the Africa\nthat you normally hear about"},{"time":17000,"text":"of death, poverty and disease."},{"time":19800,"text":"And that what I spoke about,"},{"time":21880,"text":"became part of what is known now\nas the narrative of the rising Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27360,"text":"I want to tell you two stories\nabout this rising Africa."},{"time":30720,"text":"The first has to do with Rwanda,"},{"time":32520,"text":"a country that has gone\nthrough many trials and tribulations."},{"time":35960,"text":"And Rwanda has decided to become\nthe technology hub, or a technology hub"},{"time":40480,"text":"on the continent."},{"time":41840,"text":"It's a country with mountainous\nand hilly terrain,"},{"time":44880,"text":"a little bit like here,"},{"time":46120,"text":"so it's very difficult\nto deliver services to people."},{"time":49320,"text":"So what has Rwanda said?"},{"time":51040,"text":"In order to save lives,\nit's going to try using drones"},{"time":54720,"text":"to deliver lifesaving drugs,\nvaccines and blood"},{"time":57960,"text":"to people in hard-to-reach places"},{"time":60000,"text":"in partnership with\na company called Zipline,"},{"time":62520,"text":"with UPS, and also with the Gavi,\na global vaccine alliance."},{"time":67080,"text":"In doing this, it will save lives."},{"time":69480,"text":"This is part of the type of innovation\nwe want to see in the rising Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74800,"text":"The second story has to do with something"},{"time":77360,"text":"that I'm sure most of you\nhave seen or will remember."},{"time":80400,"text":"Very often, countries in Africa\nsuffer drought and floods,"},{"time":84320,"text":"and it's getting more frequent\nbecause of climate change effects."},{"time":88040,"text":"When this happens, they normally wait\nfor international appeals to raise money."},{"time":93760,"text":"You see pictures of children\nwith flies on their faces,"},{"time":97160,"text":"carcasses of dead animals and so on."},{"time":99680,"text":"Now these countries,\n32 countries, came together"},{"time":102720,"text":"under the auspices of the African Union"},{"time":105200,"text":"and decided to form an organization\ncalled the African Risk Capacity."},{"time":110240,"text":"What does it do?"},{"time":111480,"text":"It's a weather-based insurance agency,"},{"time":113600,"text":"and what these countries do\nis to pay insurance each year,"},{"time":118000,"text":"about 3 million dollars a year\nof their own resources,"},{"time":120960,"text":"so that in the event they have\na difficult drought situation or flood,"},{"time":125800,"text":"this money will be paid out to them,"},{"time":128440,"text":"which they can then use\nto take care of their populations,"},{"time":131200,"text":"instead of waiting for aid to come."},{"time":134000,"text":"The African Risk Capacity\nlast year paid 26 million dollars"},{"time":138240,"text":"to Mauritania, Senegal and Niger."},{"time":140760,"text":"This enabled them to take care\nof 1.3 million people affected by drought."},{"time":146240,"text":"They were able to restore livelihoods,"},{"time":148600,"text":"buy fodder for cattle,\nfeed children in school"},{"time":151320,"text":"and in short keep the populations home\ninstead of migrating out of the area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157120,"text":"So these are the kinds of stories"},{"time":159000,"text":"of an Africa ready\nto take responsibility for itself,"},{"time":162640,"text":"and to look for solutions\nfor its own problems."},{"time":165840,"text":"But that narrative is being challenged now"},{"time":168360,"text":"because the continent has not\nbeen doing well in the last two years."},{"time":173200,"text":"It had been growing\nat five percent per annum"},{"time":176160,"text":"for the last one and a half decades,"},{"time":178120,"text":"but this year's forecast\nwas three percent. Why?"},{"time":180920,"text":"In an uncertain global environment,\ncommodity prices have fallen."},{"time":185120,"text":"Many of the economies\nare still commodity driven,"},{"time":188320,"text":"and therefore their\nperformance has slipped."},{"time":191480,"text":"And now the issue of Brexit\ndoesn't make it any easier."},{"time":195480,"text":"I never knew that the Brexit could happen"},{"time":199120,"text":"and that it could be one of the things\nthat would cause global uncertainty"},{"time":203280,"text":"such as we have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204600,"text":"So now we've got this situation,"},{"time":206800,"text":"and I think it's time to take stock"},{"time":209680,"text":"and to say what were the things\nthat the African countries did right?"},{"time":214560,"text":"What did they do wrong?"},{"time":216840,"text":"How do we build on all of this\nand learn lessons"},{"time":219320,"text":"so that we can keep Africa rising?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":222720,"text":"So let me talk about six things\nthat I think we did right."},{"time":226720,"text":"The first is managing\nour economies better."},{"time":230040,"text":"The '80s and '90s were the lost decades,\nwhen Africa was not doing well,"},{"time":234320,"text":"and some of you will remember\nan \"Economist\" cover"},{"time":237960,"text":"that said, \"The Lost Continent.\""},{"time":240000,"text":"But in the 2000s, policymakers learned"},{"time":244120,"text":"that they needed to manage\nthe macroeconomic environment better,"},{"time":248400,"text":"to ensure stability,"},{"time":249960,"text":"keep inflation low in single digits,"},{"time":252600,"text":"keep their fiscal deficits low,\nbelow three percent of GDP,"},{"time":258200,"text":"give investors, both domestic and foreign,"},{"time":262120,"text":"some stability so they'll have confidence\nto invest in these economies."},{"time":265960,"text":"So that was number one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267480,"text":"Two, debt."},{"time":268840,"text":"In 1994, the debt-to-GDP ratio\nof African countries was 130 percent,"},{"time":274560,"text":"and they didn't have fiscal space."},{"time":276840,"text":"They couldn't use their resources\nto invest in their development"},{"time":279880,"text":"because they were paying debt."},{"time":281360,"text":"There may be some of you in this room\nwho worked to support African countries"},{"time":286120,"text":"to get debt relief."},{"time":287440,"text":"So private creditors, multilaterals\nand bilaterals came together"},{"time":291920,"text":"and decided to do the Highly Indebted\nPoor Countries Initiative"},{"time":295560,"text":"and give debt relief."},{"time":296840,"text":"So this debt relief in 2005"},{"time":298960,"text":"made the debt-to-GDP ratio\nfall down to about 30 percent,"},{"time":302920,"text":"and there was enough resources\nto try and reinvest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306840,"text":"The third thing was\nloss-making enterprises."},{"time":309320,"text":"Governments were involved in business"},{"time":311400,"text":"which they had no business being in."},{"time":313680,"text":"And they were running businesses,\nthey were making losses."},{"time":316800,"text":"So some of these enterprises\nwere restructured,"},{"time":319560,"text":"commercialized, privatized or closed,"},{"time":322000,"text":"and they became\nless of a burden on government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326080,"text":"The fourth thing\nwas a very interesting thing."},{"time":329200,"text":"The telecoms revolution came,"},{"time":331520,"text":"and African countries jumped on it."},{"time":334120,"text":"In 2000, we had 11 million phone lines."},{"time":336760,"text":"Today, we have about 687 million\nmobile lines on the continent."},{"time":342120,"text":"And this has enabled us"},{"time":343960,"text":"to go, move forward\nwith some mobile technology"},{"time":346640,"text":"where Africa is actually leading."},{"time":349280,"text":"In Kenya, the development\nof mobile money --"},{"time":351840,"text":"M-Pesa, which all of you\nhave heard about --"},{"time":354640,"text":"it took some time for the world\nto notice that Africa was ahead"},{"time":358120,"text":"in this particular technology."},{"time":359680,"text":"And this mobile money\nis also providing a platform"},{"time":362920,"text":"for access to alternative energy."},{"time":365400,"text":"You know, people who can now pay for solar"},{"time":368920,"text":"the same way they pay\nfor cards for their telephone."},{"time":373160,"text":"So this was a very good development,\nsomething that went right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378240,"text":"We also invested more\nin education and health, not enough,"},{"time":382760,"text":"but there were some improvements."},{"time":384440,"text":"250 million children were immunized\nin the last one and a half decades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390520,"text":"The other thing was\nthat conflicts decreased."},{"time":393920,"text":"There were many conflicts\non the continent."},{"time":396000,"text":"Many of you are aware of that."},{"time":397480,"text":"But they came down, and our leaders\neven managed to dampen some coups."},{"time":402320,"text":"New types of conflicts have emerged,\nand I'll refer to those later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406400,"text":"So based on all this, there's also\nsome differentiation on the continent"},{"time":410040,"text":"that I want you to know about,"},{"time":411520,"text":"because even as\nthe doom and gloom is here,"},{"time":414040,"text":"there are some countries --\nCÃ´te d'Ivoire, Kenya, Ethiopia,"},{"time":418040,"text":"Tanzania and Senegal are performing\nrelatively well at the moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423120,"text":"But what did we do wrong?"},{"time":425280,"text":"Let me mention eight things."},{"time":426680,"text":"You have to have\nmore things wrong than right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":430360,"text":"So there are eight things we did wrong."},{"time":432760,"text":"The first was that even though we grew,\nwe didn't create enough jobs."},{"time":436800,"text":"We didn't create jobs for our youth."},{"time":438720,"text":"Youth unemployment on the continent\nis about 15 percent,"},{"time":441680,"text":"and underemployment is a serious problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445400,"text":"The second thing that we did is that\nthe quality of growth was not good enough."},{"time":450960,"text":"Even those jobs we created\nwere low-productivity jobs,"},{"time":454520,"text":"so we moved people\nfrom low-productivity agriculture"},{"time":458040,"text":"to low-productivity commerce\nand working in the informal sector"},{"time":462000,"text":"in the urban areas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464240,"text":"The third thing\nis that inequality increased."},{"time":468600,"text":"So we created more billionaires."},{"time":473600,"text":"50 billionaires worth 96 billion dollars"},{"time":476320,"text":"own more wealth than the bottom\n75 million people on the continent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481920,"text":"Poverty,"},{"time":483520,"text":"the proportion of people in poverty --\nthat's the fourth thing -- did decrease,"},{"time":487920,"text":"but the absolute numbers did not\nbecause of population growth."},{"time":492040,"text":"And population growth is something"},{"time":494640,"text":"that we don't have enough\nof a dialogue about on the continent."},{"time":498080,"text":"And I think we will need\nto get a handle on it,"},{"time":501240,"text":"particularly how we educate girls."},{"time":504520,"text":"That is the road to really working\non this particular issue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509880,"text":"The fifth thing is that we didn't invest\nenough in infrastructure."},{"time":516720,"text":"We had investment from the Chinese."},{"time":518840,"text":"That helped some countries,\nbut it's not enough."},{"time":522080,"text":"The consumption of electricity\nin Africa on the continent"},{"time":525440,"text":"in Sub-Saharan Africa\nis equivalent to Spain."},{"time":529040,"text":"The total consumption\nis equivalent to that of Spain."},{"time":532520,"text":"So many people are living in the dark,"},{"time":535200,"text":"and as the President of the African\nDevelopment Bank said recently,"},{"time":538800,"text":"Africa cannot develop in the dark."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542120,"text":"The other thing we have not done"},{"time":544280,"text":"is that our economies\nretain the same structure"},{"time":549720,"text":"that we've had for decades."},{"time":551360,"text":"So even though we've been growing,"},{"time":553040,"text":"the structure of the economies\nhas not changed very much."},{"time":555760,"text":"We are still exporting commodities,"},{"time":558360,"text":"and exporting commodities is what?\nIt's exporting jobs."},{"time":562240,"text":"Our manufacturing value-added\nis only 11 percent."},{"time":565560,"text":"We are not creating enough\ndecent manufacturing jobs for our youth,"},{"time":570120,"text":"and trade among ourselves is low."},{"time":572760,"text":"Only about 12 percent of our trade\nis among ourselves."},{"time":576280,"text":"So that's another serious problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579000,"text":"Then governance."},{"time":581120,"text":"Governance is a serious issue."},{"time":583560,"text":"We have weak institutions,"},{"time":585800,"text":"and sometimes nonexistent institutions,\nand I think this gives way for corruption."},{"time":590840,"text":"Corruption is an issue that we have not\nyet gotten a good enough handle on,"},{"time":596080,"text":"and we have to fight tooth and nail,"},{"time":598720,"text":"that and increased transparency\nin the way we manage our economies"},{"time":602320,"text":"and the way we manage our finances."}]},{"cues":[{"time":604800,"text":"We also need to be wary of new conflicts,"},{"time":609560,"text":"new types of conflicts,"},{"time":611520,"text":"such as we have with Boko Haram\nin my country, Nigeria,"},{"time":614760,"text":"and with Al-Shabaab in Kenya."},{"time":616840,"text":"We need to partner\nwith international partners,"},{"time":620200,"text":"developed countries,\nto fight this together."},{"time":623080,"text":"Otherwise, we create a new reality"},{"time":625000,"text":"which is not the type\nwe want for a rising Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628280,"text":"And finally, the issue of education."},{"time":631840,"text":"Our education systems\nin many countries are broken."},{"time":635160,"text":"We are not creating the types of skills\nneeded for the future."},{"time":639720,"text":"So we have to find a way\nto educate better."},{"time":642920,"text":"So those are the things\nthat we are not doing right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646240,"text":"Now, where do we go from there?"},{"time":649240,"text":"I believe that the way forward\nis to learn to manage success."},{"time":653960,"text":"Very often, when people succeed\nor countries succeed,"},{"time":657720,"text":"they forget what made them succeed."},{"time":660680,"text":"Learning what you're successful at,"},{"time":663240,"text":"managing it and keeping it\nis vital for us."},{"time":665680,"text":"So all those things I said we did right,"},{"time":667920,"text":"we have to learn to do it right again,\nkeep doing it right."},{"time":671840,"text":"Managing the economy while\ncreating stability is vital,"},{"time":675440,"text":"getting prices right,\nand policy consistency."},{"time":678960,"text":"Very often, we are not consistent."},{"time":681360,"text":"One regime goes out, another comes in"},{"time":683640,"text":"and they throw away even the functioning\npolicies that were there before."},{"time":687120,"text":"What does this do?"},{"time":688400,"text":"It creates uncertainty\nfor people, for households,"},{"time":690800,"text":"uncertainties for business."},{"time":692200,"text":"They don't know whether and how to invest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":694920,"text":"Debt: we must manage\nthe success we had in reducing our debt,"},{"time":699280,"text":"but now countries\nare back to borrowing again,"},{"time":701840,"text":"and we see our debt-to-GDP ratio\nbeginning to creep up,"},{"time":705280,"text":"and in certain countries,"},{"time":706760,"text":"debt is becoming a problem,\nso we have to avoid that."},{"time":709280,"text":"So managing success."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710760,"text":"The next thing\nis focusing with a laser beam"},{"time":713440,"text":"on those things we did not do well."},{"time":715320,"text":"First and foremost is infrastructure."},{"time":717200,"text":"Yes, most countries now recognize\nthey have to invest in this,"},{"time":720800,"text":"and they are trying to do\nthe best they can to do that."},{"time":723440,"text":"We must."},{"time":724680,"text":"The most important thing is power."},{"time":726360,"text":"You cannot develop in the dark."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728640,"text":"And then governance and corruption:"},{"time":730920,"text":"we have to fight."},{"time":732160,"text":"We have to make our countries transparent."},{"time":734960,"text":"And above all, we have to\nengage our young people."},{"time":738560,"text":"We have genius in our young people."},{"time":740800,"text":"I see it every day."},{"time":742080,"text":"It's what makes me wake up\nin the morning and feel ready to go."},{"time":745640,"text":"We have to unleash\nthe genius of our young people,"},{"time":748040,"text":"get out of their way,\nsupport them to create and innovate"},{"time":751320,"text":"and lead the way."},{"time":752560,"text":"And I know that they will lead us\nin the right direction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":755280,"text":"And our women, and our girls:"},{"time":757480,"text":"we have to recognize\nthat girls and women are a gift."},{"time":760560,"text":"They have strength,"},{"time":762080,"text":"and we have to unleash that strength"},{"time":764240,"text":"so that they can\ncontribute to the continent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767200,"text":"I strongly believe\nthat when we do all of these things,"},{"time":771040,"text":"we find that the rising Africa narrative"},{"time":774280,"text":"is not a fluke."},{"time":775880,"text":"It's a trend."},{"time":777720,"text":"It's a trend, and if we continue,\nif we unleash our youth,"},{"time":781560,"text":"if we unleash our women,"},{"time":782920,"text":"we may step backwards sometimes,"},{"time":784960,"text":"we may even step sideways,"},{"time":786880,"text":"but the trend is clear."},{"time":788520,"text":"Africa will continue to rise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790560,"text":"And I tell you businesspeople\nin the audience,"},{"time":794320,"text":"investment in Africa is not for today,\nis not for tomorrow,"},{"time":797800,"text":"it's not a short-term thing,\nit's a longer term thing."},{"time":801080,"text":"But if you are not invested in Africa,"},{"time":803520,"text":"then you will be missing"},{"time":804960,"text":"one of the most important\nemerging opportunities in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":809240,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":810480,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":819227,"text":"Kelly Stoetzel: So you mentioned\ncorruption in your talk,"},{"time":821920,"text":"and you're known, well-known\nas a strong anticorruption fighter."},{"time":825440,"text":"But that's had consequences."},{"time":828000,"text":"People have fought back,\nand your mother was kidnapped."},{"time":830960,"text":"How have you been handling this?"},{"time":833280,"text":"Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala:\nIt's been very difficult."},{"time":835480,"text":"Thank you for mentioning\nthe issue of the kidnap of my mother."},{"time":839840,"text":"It's a very difficult subject."},{"time":842440,"text":"But what it means\nis that when you fight corruption,"},{"time":846320,"text":"when you touch the pockets\nof people who are stealing money,"},{"time":849760,"text":"they don't just keep quiet."},{"time":851640,"text":"They fight back, and the issue for you\nis when they try to intimidate you,"},{"time":855320,"text":"do you give up, or do you fight on?"},{"time":858800,"text":"Do you find a way\nto stay on and fight back?"},{"time":861960,"text":"And the answer that I had\nwith the teams I worked with"},{"time":866240,"text":"is we have to fight on."},{"time":868040,"text":"We have to create those institutions."},{"time":869880,"text":"We have to find ways to stop these people"},{"time":873120,"text":"from taking away\nthe heritage of the future."},{"time":876320,"text":"And so that's what we did."},{"time":878240,"text":"And even out of government,\nwe continued to make that point."},{"time":881880,"text":"In our countries, nobody,\nnobody is going to fight corruption"},{"time":885880,"text":"for us but us."},{"time":887440,"text":"And therefore,\nthat comes with consequences,"},{"time":889680,"text":"and we just have to do the best we can."},{"time":891600,"text":"But I thank you and thank TED\nfor giving us a voice"},{"time":895040,"text":"to say to those people, you will not win,"},{"time":898360,"text":"and we will not be intimidated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":900720,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901960,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":903200,"text":"Kelly Stoetzel: Thank you so much\nfor your great talk and important work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":906690,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}